"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"block pha drugH1Div\" id=\"F145653\" xmlns=\"file://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">",
"    <span class=\"drugH1\">",
"     Mechanism of Action",
"    </span>",
"    <p style=\"text-indent:0em;display:inline\">",
"     Carbinoxamine competes with histamine for H",
"     <sub>",
"      1",
"     </sub>",
"     -receptor sites on effector cells in the gastrointestinal tract, blood vessels, and respiratory tract.",
"    </p>",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"block phk drugH1Div\" id=\"F145666\" xmlns=\"file://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">",
"    <span class=\"drugH1\">",
"     Pharmacodynamics/Kinetics",
"    </span>",
"    <p style=\"text-indent:-2em;margin-left:2em;\">",
"     Duration of effect: ~4 hours",
"    </p>",
"    <p style=\"text-indent:-2em;margin-left:2em;\">",
"     Metabolism: Hepatic (Simons, 2004)",
"    </p>",
"    <p style=\"text-indent:-2em;margin-left:2em;\">",
"     Excretion: Urine (Maurer, 1988)",
"    </p>",
"   </div>",
